In [effective go](https://go.googlesource.com/go/+/release-branch.go1.4/doc/effective_go.html) L1245, there are example of describe how to use composite literals to initialize `array` and `map`, 

```go
a := [...]string   {Enone: "no error", Eio: "Eio", Einval: "invalid argument"}
s := []string      {Enone: "no error", Eio: "Eio", Einval: "invalid argument"}
m := map[int]string{Enone: "no error", Eio: "Eio", Einval: "invalid argument"}
```

But these example are incorrect.
